',3),(521,1,'2015-06-02 05:52:48','2015-06-02 05:52:48','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tour][vc_tta_section title=\"Requirements\" tab_id=\"1436964612235-08dd5619-d72e\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div id=\"requirements\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\r\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\r\n	<li>No prior knowledge or experience is necessary</li>\r\n	<li>The only requirement is to bring an excitement for learning German and a willingness to give it your best effort!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"What i get\" tab_id=\"1436964612564-63dc4f66-1d4d\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<div id=\"what-you-get\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\">\r\n<ul class=\"regular-list\">\r\n	<li>Over 22 lectures and 1 hour of content!</li>\r\n	<li>Know the basic fundamentals of German grammar</li>\r\n	<li>Know how to pronounce words and speak like a German</li>\r\n	<li>Know 33 greetings and phrases to use in real life</li>\r\n	<li>Know 100 different nouns in 5 categories: People &amp; Family, Around Town, Body Parts, Food, and Animals &amp; Nature</li>\r\n	<li>Know 22 different verbs and how to use them in a sentence</li>\r\n	<li>Describe things using 20 different adjectives</li>\r\n	<li>Describe actions using 20 different adverbs</li>\r\n	<li>Know the best tools and resources to continue learning and practicing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"who-should-attend\" class=\"top-space-for-scroll\"></div>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tour][vc_column_text css=\".vc_custom_1436964877926{margin-top: 30px !important;}\"]\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">Welcome to The Best Absolute Beginner\'s Guide to Learning German!</h3>\r\nWhether you\'re wanting to live or travel in Germany or just want to learn a few basics, this course will help you <strong>carry on conversations in German</strong> in as little time as possible. Specifically, this course has been carefully designed to help you accomplish three goals:\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><em>Learn the BASIC German grammar fundamentals</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Learn how to speak like a German</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Learn the most common German words and phrases</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nI will also provide you with valuable tools and resources that will help you continue learning and practicing well beyond the end of this course.\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">What\'s inside?</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><em>22 lectures</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Over 1 hour of content</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>Easy-to-understand overview of German grammar</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>3 quizzes to help you retain what you\'ve learned</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>100 nouns</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>22 verbs with conjugations made easy</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>20 adjectives</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>20 adverbs</em></li>\r\n	<li><em>33 common greetings and other phrases</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1436965034364{margin-bottom: 10px !important;}\"][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text=\"Curriculum\" font_container=\"tag:h3|text_align:left\" google_fonts=\"font_family:Montserrat%3Aregular%2C700|font_style:700%20bold%20regular%3A700%3Anormal\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 1: Introduction\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Introduction\" meta=\"05:54\"]Why do I have a section on pronunciation? Can\'t you just learn words and phrases and be done with it? NO. I mean...yes, but don\'t you want to sound like a German? In this introduction, I show you the difference between sounding like an American speaking German and sounding like a German.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Consonants\" meta=\"05:54\"]In this lecture, you\'ll learn how to pronounce some of the most famous German consonants. If you can pronounce these right, you get a high five. Through the computer.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Vowels\" meta=\"05:54\"]German has some pretty interesting sounds, and it\'s important to know how to pronounce vowels. Why? Because they\'re everywhere! Knowing how to pronounce German vowels will help you learn faster and sound like German.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Special Characters\" meta=\"05:54\"]German uses the same alphabet as English. Or does it? Here I\'ll introduce you to three special additions to the alphabet and when they\'re used. But don\'t worry--this stuff is easy compared to Chinese![/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 2: Articles\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Cases\" meta=\"05:54\"]\"Gosh, can\'t I just start learning German phrases already?\" Patience, young one. Knowing cases will make learning German soooo much easier. Here I teach you how to know a noun\'s case, which will help you construct your own sentences, phrases, and skyscrapers (I can\'t guarantee that last one).[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Genders\" meta=\"05:54\"]German nouns have genders. Crazy, right?! That doesn\'t mean that clock on the wall will be your next date, but knowing a noun\'s gender will help you put words together and impress real-life dates. It\'s been known to happen.[/stm_course_lesson][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_film-play\" badge=\"preview\" title=\"Articles\" meta=\"05:54\"]What do you get when you put cases and genders together? Articles! Or at least that\'s what they\'re used for. Articles are words like \"a\" and \"the\", and German articles aren\'t quite as easygoing as English articles. But ne\'er fear--this lecture will teach you how to make sense of articles without getting bogged down in the details.[/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][stm_course_lessons title=\"Section 3: Conclusion\"][stm_course_lesson icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_certificate\" badge=\"quiz\" title=\"Conclusion\" meta=\"45:23\" meta_icon=\"fa-icon-stm_icon_doc_edit\"]You made it! I couldn\'t be more proud. Here we review what you\'ve learned, and I provide some tools that will help you continue learning. Keep up the good work, and you\'ll be speaking like a native in no time![/stm_course_lesson][/stm_course_lessons][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Learn Basic German Fast','German for Beginners online video course is designed as an easy to use, fun and interactive introduction to the German language. It\'s ideal for people wanting to travel or live in Germany. This course will teach you the structures and vocabulary necessary in order to communicate in every day situations.','publish','open','closed','','learn-basic-german','','','2015-08-05 06:21:48','2015-08-05 06:21:48','',0,'http://masterstudy.stylemixthemes.com/demo/?post_type=product&#038;p=521',0,'product','',1),(523,1,'2015-06-02 05:55:12','2015-06-02 05:55:12','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3 style=\"margin-bottom: 30px;\">The Founder Institute presents \"Become a Startup Founder\" - the first online program designed to teach you everything you need to know to launch your startup.</h3>\r\nBecome a Startup Founder is a comprehensive step-by-step program to help Founders launch a meaningful and enduring technology company at their own pace.\r\n\r\nThe curriculum and the assignments are based on the intensive four-month <a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://fi.co/r/udemy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Founder Institute</a> program, an entrepreneur training and startup launch program that has helped launch hundreds of successful companies across the globe, like Udemy. The <strong>more than 55 videos</strong> organized in this offering represent the most inspirational, most informative and best-rated talks by leading CEOs